remarks.para:
.Net Logger is a thread-safe system for storing and representation of various log messages. Besides text messages, programmer 
            can associate with data any object that can carry extended information. For example, it can be a price snapshot, quantity value of a product or a pointer 
            to the product object. When a programmer analyzes a log file, he can not just review messages, but also vizw product characteristics that can be dynamically changed. 
            There are several possibilities of object association:  


Creating a hierarchical representation of associated object's properties and its values

Displaying a list of properties with its values in a popup tooltip

Transferring an object associated with message to the .Net Inspector for detailed viewing and editing


